3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a text readability index as a core feature of the technique, which could potentially involve machine learning algorithms for its computation. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a technique that involves processing natural language text to extract information-rich content, which is a key task in artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.DL (Deep Learning) - The paper mentions tasks like keyphrase indexing and extracting sentences describing protein interactions, which could potentially involve deep learning techniques for their implementation.
